---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Has Some Customers - CXO Atlas',
  description: 'Early customer validation and revenue generation. Get practical guidance for entrepreneurs with their first paying customers.',
  keywords: 'first customers, customer validation, revenue generation, customer acquisition, startup growth',
  canonical: 'https://cxo-atlas.com/article/has-some-customers'
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <Hero
    title="Has Some Customers"
    subtitle="Early customer validation and revenue generation. Get practical guidance for entrepreneurs with their first paying customers."
    actions={[
      { text: 'Browse All Articles', href: '/article', variant: 'primary' },
      { text: 'Back to Journey Map', href: '/#journey' },
    ]}
    image={{ src: '~/assets/images/hero-image.png', alt: 'Has Some Customers' }}
  />

  <Content
    id="has-customers-content"
    class="py-16 md:py-24"
    background="light"
  >
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2>Stage 5: Has Some Customers</h2>
        
        <p>Congratulations! You have paying customers. This is a huge milestone - you've proven that people are willing to pay for what you're offering. Now it's time to understand why and scale it.</p>

        <h3>What This Stage Looks Like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You have paying customers who value your product/service</li>
          <li>You're generating consistent revenue</li>
          <li>You're learning what drives customer satisfaction</li>
          <li>You're building customer relationships</li>
          <li>You're identifying your most successful sales channels</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Key Challenges</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Customer Retention:</strong> Keeping your existing customers happy</li>
          <li><strong>Scaling Sales:</strong> Finding more customers like your best ones</li>
          <li><strong>Product Development:</strong> Balancing new features with stability</li>
          <li><strong>Customer Support:</strong> Managing growing customer needs</li>
          <li><strong>Financial Management:</strong> Managing cash flow with real revenue</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What You Need to Know</h3>
        <p>This stage is about understanding your success and replicating it. You need to identify what makes your best customers successful and find more people like them.</p>

        <h3>Critical Focus Areas</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer success and satisfaction</li>
          <li>Sales process optimization</li>
          <li>Product-market fit validation</li>
          <li>Customer acquisition scaling</li>
          <li>Revenue predictability and growth</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Success Metrics</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer lifetime value (CLV)</li>
          <li>Customer acquisition cost (CAC)</li>
          <li>Monthly recurring revenue (MRR)</li>
          <li>Customer retention and churn rates</li>
          <li>Net Promoter Score (NPS)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Next Steps</h3>
        <p>When you need more capital to grow faster than your current revenue allows, you're entering the "Needs to Raise Money" stage. This is where you consider external funding.</p>

        <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-500">
          <h4>ðŸ’° Pro Tip</h4>
          <p>Focus on customer success over customer acquisition. Happy customers will refer others and provide valuable feedback. It's easier to grow with satisfied customers than to constantly acquire new ones.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Content>

  <CallToAction
    id="customers-cta"
    class="py-16 md:py-24"
    background="dark"
    title="Ready to Scale with Funding?"
    subtitle="Get guidance for raising capital to accelerate growth."
    actions={[
      { text: 'Needs to Raise Money', href: '/article/needs-to-raise-money', variant: 'primary' },
      { text: 'Browse All Articles', href: '/article' },
    ]}
  />
</Layout>
